title: For Sale/Trade:  Early (preproduction?) Colt Delta Elite 10mm 1911
postcontent:
For sale and/or trade consideration is a very early Colt Delta Elite 10mm 1911 pistol in a blued finish - Very nice original condition with few handling marks; minimal signs of normal finish wear. Includes (1) original Colt 10mm magazine.

What makes this particular example interesting is that per the Colt serial number on the frame, that it's a Colt Government model frame, manufactured in 1985; the Delta Elite became commercially available in 1986, so it has been advised to me by a reputable Colt collector that this is one of the first Delta Elites that utilized left over Government frames. Upon sending pictures to a historian at Colt, as I suspected and was confirmed, the gun was never refinished by Colt and appears original. 

Early blued Colt Delta Elite's are hard to find and this is a very unique early Colt Delta Elite and a great shooter!

$1,550 and/or possible partial handgun trade. Feel free to email and I'll respond promptly. 

Must be a Wisconsin resident and willing to sign a bill of sale. I have a Wisconsin CCL that I'm happy to show you for your peace of mind. Thanks!
